         <h2>So here's what happened on the Train</h2>
        <p>Here are some of the highlights (and lowlights) riding the Train to the Grand Canyon</p>
        <p>One thing that became a minor concern on the train was when Mike, the Train Guy, informed us that the toilets burp; therefore, we needed to keep the lid on when flushing. It also appeared that the bathroom nearest us was a dinky toilet,
            with a foldable sink. After passing the passerby's who love being waved at (making their day) and the Prairie Dog Village, where the Prairie Dog's roam, we were off to the Grand Canyon, with desert scenery and Ponderosa Pines that
            would make Bend, Oregon jealous with envy.</p>
