        </div>
        <p>One thing that made the Bodie's giggle and laugh was a sign to a place called Pitt Tank Road. Unfortunately, Adam did not get the message, enjoying a nice soothing shit in the dinky toilet. By the time Adam realized this, it was too
            late. Fortunately, by taking the Train there, they had to take the Train back.</p>
        <p>Everyone on the train wished Adam a Happy 30th Birthday, even telling him personally afterwards. They thought his hat was quite clever</p>
        <p>The only person who seemed offended was Marshal Bill, who wanted me to get him a present. I told him "Where's my present?" He asked, "Should your birthday be all about you then?" which Adam replied "Hell Yeah!"</p>
        <p>Jenn, on the other hand, wanted to make sure everyone knew about a bruise she had recently gotten rid of after having it for a while: A long hot dog shaped purple bruise she got in Maryland that turned yellow before going away. Debbi
            told Jenn to be quiet and not to let everyone know about it. Jenn, unfazed, seemed to be interested in speaking loud and proud, which Adam remarked "Let's get her a microphone!" Finally, she was offered one by Mike the Train Guy.
            At that point, Jenn kept quiet.</p>
        <p>Perhaps the most shocking moment of them all didn't occur in the dome. Wanting to join her brother outside, Jenn looked at the tracks, heard the tracks make beautiful rhythm, and at that moment, decided to dance to the tracks. What
            Jenn didn't know what that the people inside were watching her the whole time, deeming Jenn's dancing excellent and eventful. Jenn left to go back to her seat, declaring "I'll be back for more later...‚Äù Jenn returned outside two
