         <h2>Some interesting facts at the Grand Canyon Railway</h2>
        <p>The whole route runs 64 miles, going from Williams, to the Grand Canyon</p>
        <p>It began in 1901, built by the Santa Fe Railway, who owned it until 1968, when trains became less popular than automobiles.</p>
        <p>The railway was eventually started up again after being purchased by Max and Thelma Biegert, a wealthy couple from Phoenix.</p>
        <p>They eventually sold it to its current owners, the Xanterra Parks & Resorts group, originally known as the Fred Harvey Company.</p>
        <p>Fred Harvey must be special, because that's the part of the train we were on!</p>
